Yessenov Launch Pad 2025
PLEASE CAREFULLY STUDY THE PROVISIONS OF THE PROGRAM AT THE BOTTOM OF THE PAGE.
The Shakhmardan Yessenov Foundation provides ten (10) grants for additional training in hard skills and/or soft skills.
If you are:
- A citizen of the Republic of Kazakhstan;
- Student from Kazakhstani university or working professional;
- Specializing in natural sciences, mathematics and statistics, information and communication technologies, engineering, manufacturing and construction industries and healthcare.
- You want to upgrade your soft and/or hard skills.
You have the chance to BECOME A GRANT WINNER AND take online/offline training up to 12 months!
The grant amount is 600 000 tenge!
To do so submit your application down below, including the following documents before October 14, 2025.
Required documents:
- Scan of the identity card;
- Аn essay explaining why he/she needs additional skills and how they will affect his/her professional and personal life;
- СV.
Additional documents:
- A portfolio showcasing the candidate’s achievements and/or expressed interests in a specific area, in accordance with clause 3.1. of Provisions, and provide relevant evidence – no more than three (3) documents;
- Recommendations – no more than one (1) document;
- Certificates confirming academic achievements, success in research and/or engineering activities, participation in conferences, seminars of different levels – no more than three (3) documents*;
- Own, collaborative publications – no more than two (2) publications;
- Diploma (last place of study), if available – no more than one (1) document;
- Social activities and volunteering certificates – no more than two (2) certificates*
*The Foundation considers a limited number of certificates. The candidate must independently select the certificates that best showcase his/her achievements.
